  <static seed="1586" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalEquations/solveRationalEquations25.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve the equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ {\frac{r}{2r+12}+\frac{6}{r+6}}={-1}  }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="31" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left\{-8\right\}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To clear fractions in an equation, multiply each side of the equation by a common denominator. For this problem, a common denominator is <m>{2\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
  {\frac{r}{2r+12}+\frac{6}{r+6}} \amp = {-1} \\
  {\frac{r}{2\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)}+\frac{6}{r+6}} \amp = {-1} \\
  {\frac{r}{2\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)}\cdot 2\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)+\frac{6}{r+6}\cdot 2\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)} \amp = {-2\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)} \\
  {r+12} \amp = {-2r-12} \\
  {r+2r} \amp = {-12-12} \\
  {3r} \amp = {-24} \\
  \frac{{3r}}{3} \amp = \frac{{-24}}{3} \\
  r \amp = -8
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>We must check solutions when we solve rational equations. In the original equation, both denominators cannot be <m>0</m>. We set them to <m>0</m>, so we can find out what values to exclude from the solution set.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \amp 2r+12 = 0 \amp \;\amp  r+6=0 \\
   \amp 2r = -12 \amp \;\amp  r=-6 \\
   \amp \frac{2r}{2} = \frac{-12}{2} \\
   \amp r = -6 \\
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>We must exclude <m>-6</m> from the solution set. This value is not in the solution set we got, so the final solution is <m>r=-8</m>.</p>
</solution>
